Column Comment.0: FOSSIL NAME SET IDENTIFIER: Unique Identifier for a fossil name set.
Column Comment.1: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.2: AREA IDENTIFIER: The unique identifier for the area in which this fossil name set isvalid.
Column Comment.3: AREA TYPE: the type of area described. In this case, could be FOSSIL NAME SETor BIOSTRATIGRAPHIC BASIN.
Column Comment.4: CERTIFIED INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this fossil name set has beencertified by an appropriate scientific authority. Uncertified name sets may be used forworking purposes or preliminary analysis. Final work should be converted toacertified name set before archival.
Column Comment.5: EFFECTIVE DATE: date on which the data in this row came into effect.
Column Comment.6: EXPIRY DATE: Date on which the data in this row of data was no longer in effect.
Column Comment.7: FOSSIL NAME SET TYPE: The type of fossil name set, such as MMS, GSC, workingor archival.
Column Comment.8: FOSSIL NAME SET NAME: the common name given to this fossil name set.
Column Comment.9: BUSINESS ASSOCIATE OWNER: the unique identifier for the business associatewho is the owner of this stratigraphic name set, such as the MMS, AGSO, USGS,GSC etc.
Column Comment.10: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.11: PREFERRED INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this is the name set that ispreferred for use at this installation. Generally, the preferred name set will also becertified.
Column Comment.12: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.13: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.14: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.15: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.16: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.17: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.18: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.19: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.20: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
